Diet and Cairn Maintence

Diet

I feed as natural and healthy as possible, nothing but premium food such as Open farm and fresh foods that I cook and bake for them. Before and during pregnancies I feed an organic blend of prenatal vitamins to help ensure the best possible chance of a healthy pregnancy and delivery for my dams and their puppies. Open Farm provides human-grade quality food, employs small farms, and produces a very healthy dog food! I feed open farm food to all my adult dogs and puppies. One of the best parts of open farm is there ingredients list is all able to be traced back to its source through their website. With Open Farm you know exactly what's in our furry friend's food and exactly where it came from. My adult dogs are a fan of all the dry dog foods, they have had all the stews as a topper to dry dog food, bone broth is something I buy often for a treat and each bone broth bag lasts quite a while and they all love it! The training treats are amazing and the freeze-dried food is a favorite as well! My adult dogs and puppies I provide have an amazing quality of life and health and one of the reasons to thank for that is Open Farm! (i am not an affiliate, I do not get paid for telling anyone about Open Farm)

Alone time

Just like most other dogs Cairn's do Not like to be left alone for extended period of time, like more then 8 hours a day, if they are left alone that long or longer you can experience destructive behavior from your cairn like barking or

Other Foods

The only other food type item I recommend is called a no hide from Earth Animals. No hide is a rawhide alternative that won't wreak havoc on your furry friend's digestive track as rawhides will. No hide is a great healthy treat that I make sure I always have around, It is one of the only things I can buy that they can't chew up in 20 mins and its made with healthy ingredients!

What not to feed

My general rule of thumb for food is if Walmart sells it i don't feed it. Not because of Walmart but because of the food quality. The only food I would ever come close to recommending from Walmart is a fresh pet select, you should be safe with pretty much any of the fresh pet select food options.
